PHASE 2 BEHAVIOR VERIFIED
- New defenses begin at Tier 0.
- Upgrades proceed one tier at a time and require the matching civilization level.
- Upgrade resources are consumed only after final validation.
- Upgrade failures leave resources, tier and HP unchanged.
- Upgrades preserve the current HP percentage instead of healing the facility.
- Ruined facilities cannot be upgraded before repair.
- Tier 4 is the maximum.
- Tier-specific names, HP and operating statistics are used by live combat.
- Legacy facilities normalize to deterministic tier HP while preserving damage percentage.
- Wall-to-gate conversion begins at Tier 2 and preserves damage percentage.
- Defense and civilization panels show current tier, next tier, stat changes, cost and lock reason.
- Small-screen defense panels use bounded scrolling and sticky action controls.

ISSUES FOUND AND CORRECTED
1. The previous upgrade action restored facilities to full HP; upgrades now preserve damage percentage.
2. Tower/support durability used cumulative runtime multiplication; every tier now has an explicit deterministic HP value.
3. Selected facilities did not consistently show the actual tier name and next-tier differences; the details panel now uses tier definitions directly.
4. Upgrade costs and civilization/resource locks were not visible before confirmation; they are now displayed and invalid actions are disabled.
5. Two single-target facility names contained wording that could be mistaken for a rejected monitoring facility; they were renamed to clearly describe attack facilities.
6. The expanded upgrade preview could make the mobile detail panel too tall; bounded scrolling and sticky controls were added.

